contents:
Went here with a friend for the first time. Saw a random bouncer looking guy standing outside of a coffee shop. There&rsquo;s a door next to the coffee shop that leads into an apartment complex. My friend and I looked at each other. We were thinking we were suppose to open this door, and that this &ldquo;speak easy&rdquo; is somewhere in this apartment complex. We tried to open the door, but it wouldn&rsquo;t turn at all. We stood there with a confused look in our faces as we check the address again. The random bouncer guy asked, &ldquo;Are you guys looking for the bar?&rdquo;
I replied, &ldquo;Yeah, the address to this Bathtub Gin bar points here.&rdquo; He busts out laughing and says, &ldquo;Fellas, walk inside here.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Sir, we&rsquo;re looking for the bar and not a coffee shop.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Just step inside.&rdquo;
We walk into the coffee shop, and a door randomly opens leading into the bar. Random.
Cool bar. There&rsquo;s a bathtub in the middle. It&rsquo;s super loud at night inside. The drinks are pretty good too.
